      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TAKE HIS CASH (2) started big odds last time but hit the ground running with a slick early split, giving a sight but fading out of it to finish fourth (17.02) at this track over 300m. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Has ability and can bounce back. ECCENTRIC MONA (1) comes off an average effort last start when sixth at this track over 350m behind Zawadi (20.60) in a T3 RSTW. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Must be included in calculations. WHATEVER THRILL (7) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by 0.8 lengths at Warragul in a handy 23.14 beating Bernardo Split. Has definite claims. CRACKED GEM (4) is a last-start placegetter at this track and distance - should be thereabouts.",
